<subSubSection pageId="190" pageNumber="191" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="190.[151,1437,153,972]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,801,827]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2020" box="[568,711,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Apanteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palliditegula">
<emphasis box="[568,711,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">palliditegula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” derives from the Latin “pallidus” and “tegula”, referring to the pale yellowish tegula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="190" pageNumber="191" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="190.[151,1437,153,972]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,873,899]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Chen" authorityName="Liu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2020" box="[599,894,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Apanteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="190" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosus" status="sp.">
<emphasis box="[599,710,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">A. setosus</emphasis>
Liu &amp; Chen, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[861,894,873,899]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[861,894,873,899]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[900,949,873,899]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">nov.</emphasis>
, but differs in the following: pubescence on disc of mesonotum normal (much longer and silky on posterior half in latter); scutellum shiny and polished entirely (with long pubescence and distinctly punctate in latter); and tegula pale (dark brown in latter).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
